Package: findMean
Title: Find mean of columns according to groups and add it to original tibble
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Kashish", "Doshi", , "kdoshi@bccrc.ca", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Add a mean column to data-frame after grouping by another column. The new mean column name will add a "mean." prefix to the original column name ("mean.col_name"). This function uses the mutate [dplyr::mutate()] function and group_by [dplyr::group_by()] from the dplyr package.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
